# Three ingestion patterns

Every source falls into one of three shapes — this drives every later choice.

## Batch · incremental · streaming

- **Batch** — the full dataset every time; simple, but wasteful when only 1% changed
- **Incremental** — only new/changed records since the last load; most production ingestion lives here
- **Streaming** — records flow in continuously, target updates within seconds — same engine, continuous trigger

## Exam vocabulary

- **`Trigger.AvailableNow`** (was `Trigger.Once`) — process what's there, then stop (micro-batch on a cron)
- **`Trigger.ProcessingTime`** — fire every N seconds/minutes (continuous)
- **Checkpoint location** — offsets already processed, so a restart resumes exactly-once
